# FEMAT Website Design & Architecture Rule

See [DESIGN_DOCUMENT.md](mdc:DESIGN_DOCUMENT.md) for full details.

## Key Points
- **Framework:** Nuxt.js (Vue 3, SSR, TypeScript, Composition API)
- **UI:** Nuxt UI (built on Tailwind CSS)
- **State:** Pinia (Setup Store syntax)
- **Content:** Nuxt Content (Markdown in `content/`)
- **i18n:** @nuxtjs/i18n (French/English, JSON in `i18n/`)
- **Images:** @nuxt/image
- **Deployment:** NuxtHub, Vercel, or Netlify (CI/CD from GitHub)

## Directory Structure
- `assets/`: Images, fonts, stylesheets
- `components/`: Reusable Vue components
- `content/`: Markdown content (news, clubs, etc.)
- `layouts/`: Main layouts
- `i18n/`: Translation files (e.g., `fr.json`, `en.json`)
- `pages/`: Views and routing
- `server/`: Backend logic (if needed)
- `composables/`: Vue composables
- `store/`: Pinia stores

## UI/UX
- Mali flag colors: Green (`#14B8A6`), Yellow (`#FBBF24`), Red (`#EF4444`)
- Font: Inter or Poppins
- Responsive, mobile-first, accessible

## Content & Data
- All content managed via Nuxt Content in Markdown
- All UI text/labels managed via JSON translation files in `i18n/`

## Deployment
- GitHub as code host
- CI/CD triggers on push to `main`
- Locale-aware routing and redirection

**Always follow the architectural and tech stack decisions in [DESIGN_DOCUMENT.md](mdc:DESIGN_DOCUMENT.md).**